Each time the staff has ruined the ambiance with their extremely loud and obnoxious conversations and laughter. I really don’t want to be mean but it’s ridiculous the volume they are talking about intimate topics and using cuss words. Every time I have come. It’s unprofessional and it’s disappointing when you are trying to enjoy your coffee and relax. I understand talking and bonding with coworkers, but there’s a way to do it without shouting your conversation throughout the entire place, disturbing the peace of others. This is not a busy bar environment, it’s a coffee shop. This is the only flaw with the place.

reviews_data.review_text:
Second coffee today and I enjoyed it while working on my laptop. Yes, Summit is a great spot for your out-of-office office and sitting with your computer for a while. I was here for about two hours this morning and it was perfect.

The baristas made me an excellent cortado in a coffee cup. Two shots of espresso with an equivalent amount of steamed (not foamed) milk. Just delightful to get the same amount of caffeine without having ten more ounces of milk in it!

The seating is comfortable and the background noise was low. This was an excellent spot to work from my laptop.

reviews_data.review_text: I was in Charlotte for an event and just googled closest coffeehouse near me. Summit popped up and I am so glad. First the service was wonderful. Both of the ladies there smiled the entire time, taking orders and making coffee. It seemed like they actually loved their jobs and these days that’s rare. So 5⭐️ for the customer service. It was a cute shop but I honestly was in and out after my coffee was done. I’m sure if you had time to lounge there it would be nice. I also loved the art in bathroom (random I know) but those tiny details make huge differences. Okay now to the coffee. I ordered a Large Lavender Latte with 2 extra shots of espresso & oat milk. I also grabbed the granola to eat in the car for my long drive home. That coffee was so dang good I didn’t even get a photo. It had the perfect amount of lavender & foam. I mean it was silky and so easy to drink. Had they not been closed on my way home I would’ve returned to get a second cup. The granola was yummy too, a bit messy in the car but I had enough when I got home the next morning I used it on my yogurt and it was delicious. Wondering can I order and have it shipped? Any ways this little gem is a must try!!!!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for the kind and detailed review Briana!! We're so glad you happened upon us during your visit and hope to see you again soon!

Shipping of granola is not normally available but if you really want some... email funderburg@summitcoffee.com and we can brainstorm on it ;)

- Will, Co-owner

I really like Summit Coffee! The interior is modern and cozy, with comfortable chairs, and it’s a quiet place to work or study. They have good coffee and pastries, including a vegan pumpkin chocolate chip bar that my son devoured quickly.

I also appreciate that the space is kid-friendly! There are coloring pages and crayons, board books as well as some paperback novels and board games. There’s also a stepstool in the bathroom for reaching the sink.

I got the strawberries and cream coffee (seasonal drink) and it was so good! I think when I visited before, I had a lavender latte and that was yummy. They also will substitute oat or almond milk without an upcharge.

It’s located in a new shopping center on The Plaza, with a few other businesses in the same building. They have a nice outdoor patio.

I love this location because there is ample parking, it’s easy to access on my way to and fro, and there’s plenty of seating both inside and on the patio. They do also have an app available that is very functional and allows mobile ordering as well as a rewards program - great for busy mornings.
